                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5231/370: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-11-07T13:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1924—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. Department’s 44, October 7, 5 p.m. In reply to note October 14, Acting
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs insists that a prorogation of treaty November 5,
                        1923,<note n="15" xml:id="d603fn15">By exchange of notes Oct. 6 and 22,
                        1923, <ref target="frus1923v02#pg_873">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 873</ref>.</note> was the reply of the
                    Spanish Government to the first proposal and that prorogation on May 5th last
                    was the reply of the Spanish Government to Department’s second proposal, neither
                    draft being considered satisfactory.</p>
                <p>I should appreciate Department’s sending at once draft of a purely commercial
                    treaty containing irreducible minimum and hope that it can be cabled, as knowing
                    circumstances here I think that the matter should be presented within a few
                    weeks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
